Sentencas: FeAl and FeAl/TiC coatings are deposited by shrouded plasma spraying.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: The microstructure of the as-sprayed and annealed coatings is characterized by scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the coatings along the direction parallel to the coating surface is measured.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: Results show that the as-sprayed coatings exhibit lower electrical conductivity than that of the corresponding bulks, which is due to their inherent lamellar microstructure.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: The thin interlamellar gaps become more spherical pores and the metallurgical bonding regions are increased by high-temperature annealing due to solid-state diffusion between flattened splats.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of the coatings increases with the increase of the annealing time.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: The room temperature electrical conductivity of the coatings annealed at 1100 degrees C for over 10 h reaches to about 90% of that of the corresponding bulks.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: Besides, it is found that the electrical conductivity of the FeAl/TiC coatings increases with the increase of the TiC content.
Titulo: Effect of TiC addition and high-temperature annealing on the microstructure and electrical conductivity of shrouded-plasma-sprayed FeAl/TiC composites for SOFC support

Sentencas: When 45 vol.% TiC is added into the FeAl matrix, the electrical conductivity of the FeAl/TiC coating annealed at 1100 degrees C reaches 5.35 x 10(3)
